parse: Interrogative / Indefinite Pronoun - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: Who, which, what, why. Probably emphatic of tis; an interrogative pronoun, who, which or what.

parse: Verb - Future Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Singular
str2: To treat badly, afflict, embitter, make angry. From kakos; to injure; figuratively, to exasperate.

parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Accusative 2nd Person Plural
str2: You. The person pronoun of the second person singular; thou.
If. From ei and an; a conditional particle; in case that, provided, etc.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Middle - 2nd Person Plural
str2: A prolongation and middle voice form of a primary verb; to cause to be, i.e. to become, used with great latitude.
One who is eagerly devoted to a person or a thing, a zealot. From zeloo; a 'zealot'.
The, the definite article. Including the feminine he, and the neuter to in all their inflections; the definite article; the.
